# 3. State Model (Critical)

Every API must return explicit states.

## 3.1 Account State

-   onboarding
-   active
-   billing_hold
-   compliance_hold
-   suspended

## 3.2 Module State

-   available
-   restricted
-   pending
-   onboarding_required

## 3.3 Billing State

-   current
-   overdue
-   failed

Frontend must only **display**, never derive.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

# 4. Launch Model (Module Execution)

``` json
{
  "launch": {
    "method": "native | embed | sso | redirect",
    "url": "",
    "requires_auth": true
  }
}
```

Rules: - No raw URLs exposed without backend validation - All launches
governed by platform shell

------------------------------------------------------------------------

# 5. Role-Based Visibility

APIs must include role context:

``` json
{
  "meta": {
    "role": "client_admin | user | platform_admin"
  }
}
```

Frontend uses this to: - show/hide navigation - adjust UI states

